natural problem:
Let \[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
2x + 7 & \text{if } x < -2, \\
-x^2 - x + 1 & \text{if } x \ge -2.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find the sum of all values of $x$ such that $f(x) = -5.$

a_3.informal problem:
Find the value of $x$ that satisfies the following conditions: 
If $x < -2$, then $f(x) = 2x + 7$; 
If $x \geq -2$, then $f(x) = -x^2 - x + 1$;
And $f(x) = -5$.
The final answer is $x = -4$.
